cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.DB, cs.NI

The paper discusses the challenges and efficiencies of combining new techniques with real ultra-low latency (ULL) SSDs, which are related to data centers (cs.DC) and operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also analyzes the efficiencies of different I/O completion methods, which are related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper considers different access patterns and queues, which are related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
